The paper discusses a method for analyzing inter-relationships between RDF Graphs, which are commonly used in the semantic web. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for semantic search, databases (cs.DB) for managing RDF data, machine learning (cs.LG) for identifying patterns in the relationships between graphs, software engineering (cs.SE) for designing criteria for inter-relationships, and information retrieval (cs.IR) for searching and retrieving relevant RDF Graphs.
